spanGrp.span: My grandma says that when they arrived here there were no people; there was nothing.
Yís mamita të she-nã jie-wa desãũ-lo Ji wa jera ka pe ta yesö' ka yorö ta
all there was was a huge jungle.
ka yorö kunã ta kebiye rö kã'yaka wa jebu nẽ siganã komĩ' Je wa (_) bö nẽ siganãgẽ rö
My grandma says that when they arrived here, she came and her mother lived in Valle de la Estrella.
Yís mamita í she (_) beteũ-te rö jie mĩnã je ser-gẽ rö Valle de la Estrella
She came from there to live here.
jega jie beteũ-te jiwa desãũ-nẽ jiwa sẽ-nã'
They took a place called Ogañãk.
Jie-wa të kã' gugá kie í të Ogañãk ska
Je nẽ tögapa í siga-wa da-te-nẽ
Jeska jeska jie-wa të kã' kie rö Sapariñãk ska
She lived for a long time;
My grandma says that the place was different. My grandpa went to work and left her with my grandma, I mean, my mother.
Yís mam (r) mam (r) mamita të she-nã kã' rö jaulë ra yís tatiga mi-gẽũ shkablö të jie je-ge-tanã yís mami (r) (_) mamita ra mama je-gẽ-tanã
He went to work far away; there was no place nearby to work.
Kã' komĩ' janã mĩnã-nẽ shkablö ka mãĩ shkablö-gle ta nẽ serka nẽ
They went to work there, far away.
Jega jie-wa mi-gẽũ-lo-nẽ shkablö komĩ' wa
So, my grandma went to work with them;
Jera yís mamita bö mi-gẽũ-mĩ shkablö jie-wa ra
she would hunt the meat in the bush with the dogs.
Je të jirö te-gẽ yeke tsõ kã' dikinã te-gẽ chichi wa
They lived just on that. In order to buy clothes, my grandpa had to go to work there.
Bikö je wa jebö nẽ wa jie-wa se-nã' sua bi jirö bi tuã-glö-ra
Later on, many more people came to live there.
Tatiga janã mĩnãũ-nẽ jega shkablö je tögapa nẽ kepa pe taba-nã-ka se-nã' se-nã' jeska rö (_) kenãnãra ñãyigira
But people say that long ago there were not so many good people here.
Yís ma/ (_) siga-wa të she-ra nã ka pe ta böi
My father is from here but my grandma is from there.
Yís kaga rö jiwa ta yís mamita je deũ rö jamĩwa
Many came from there. Thus long ago people lived differently; the houses were different;
Je jie-wa deu-lo je wa tã'i ata nãyigira jebi (_) rö jaulë jie-wa jũ rö jaulë
they drank in calabashes, ate [their food] on leaves, but now we don’t thave that.
jie-wa di yu-gẽ rö tkã' nã kã'gö jãrga Ata jira sa nẽ ka wã je ta ñã sa (r) sa ianã'-wã rö
We have changed ourselves and only look at the whites’ things; glasses, spoons, plates are different.
sa të pe delí bö nẽ suẽ-gẽ pe baso pe kuchara pe plato rö jaulë
Long ago they had calabashes and leaves, and ate and drank on them.
Ñayigira jie-wa rö tkã' bö Kã'gö bö jãrga jie-wa yugö-gẽ di yu-gẽ
My grandma, my grandpa, my aunts, the elders lived like that.
Jebi yís (_) mamita-wa tatiga-wa shtö kayegé shtö keglö-wa senẽ-l
Long ago it used to be like that, not like it is today.
kã'_ñãjiñã ra je rö jebi ka rö jira jibi nẽ (m)
